WEBVTT

00:00:28.169 --> 00:00:30.849
Welcome back to the library studio here as

00:00:30.910 --> 00:00:32.450
part of the vlog.

00:00:32.509 --> 00:00:33.729
I'm your host, Craig Wynn.

00:00:34.189 --> 00:00:36.369
We're going to continue our story on

00:00:36.450 --> 00:00:37.591
returning to the garden.

00:00:38.110 --> 00:00:39.310
And you might think, well,

00:00:39.831 --> 00:00:42.070
didn't we already finish the testimony

00:00:42.351 --> 00:00:45.591
regarding the garden when we did previous

00:00:45.631 --> 00:00:46.192
programs?

00:00:46.292 --> 00:00:49.192
Now we're in the midst of Numbers five

00:00:49.253 --> 00:00:50.893
and the story of the garden is told

00:00:50.953 --> 00:00:53.613
in Genesis two and three.

00:00:53.954 --> 00:00:55.713
And indeed, that would be correct.

00:00:56.374 --> 00:00:59.034
except that the conclusion of the story

00:00:59.395 --> 00:01:02.494
regarding the garden actually talks about

00:01:02.576 --> 00:01:05.156
whether or not we return by way of

00:01:05.316 --> 00:01:07.216
ash or we return to dust.

00:01:07.777 --> 00:01:12.158
And so God is bringing our attention to

00:01:12.397 --> 00:01:16.039
what happens as a result of Numbers five,

00:01:16.558 --> 00:01:20.260
where Israel is viewed as religiously

00:01:20.299 --> 00:01:20.799
corrupt.

00:01:21.737 --> 00:01:23.099
And Dowd,

00:01:23.138 --> 00:01:25.959
who is the groom of Numbers Five,

00:01:26.019 --> 00:01:27.581
wants his bride back,

00:01:27.900 --> 00:01:30.361
and he wants her unsullied so that she

00:01:30.402 --> 00:01:35.004
is no longer corrupted by having too much

00:01:35.063 --> 00:01:37.105
indulgence into false religion.

00:01:39.078 --> 00:01:42.500
This is how we are going to determine

00:01:43.260 --> 00:01:45.340
whether or not souls, in the end,

00:01:45.600 --> 00:01:47.281
are returned to the dust of the earth,

00:01:47.320 --> 00:01:49.320
just ceasing to exist,

00:01:50.022 --> 00:01:53.281
or if they are purged by the ash

00:01:53.382 --> 00:01:55.843
of the sacrifice of the Adamah Parah,

00:01:56.403 --> 00:01:59.724
and therefore get to go on and witness

00:02:00.304 --> 00:02:01.123
Dowd's return,

00:02:01.864 --> 00:02:04.004
the great homecoming and family reunion,

00:02:04.045 --> 00:02:04.305
and then

00:02:04.840 --> 00:02:07.483
have the opportunity to reenter the Garden

00:02:07.783 --> 00:02:08.563
of Eden.

00:02:09.084 --> 00:02:12.186
So what we're reading now is the story

00:02:12.385 --> 00:02:16.929
of what will determine whether or not your

00:02:17.030 --> 00:02:21.252
soul is allowed to return to the garden.

00:02:22.092 --> 00:02:25.055
So it certainly seems as if it would

00:02:25.094 --> 00:02:28.598
be more than appropriate for us to

00:02:29.138 --> 00:02:31.278
continue our series on returning to the

00:02:31.299 --> 00:02:33.381
garden in this discussion.

00:02:35.045 --> 00:02:36.426
Now, by way of recap,

00:02:37.728 --> 00:02:42.050
we have recently come to deduce insights

00:02:42.111 --> 00:02:44.573
that have never previously been

00:02:44.653 --> 00:02:45.193
considered.

00:02:46.514 --> 00:02:51.019
An entirely different and more accurate

00:02:51.058 --> 00:02:54.781
way to evaluate what transpired in the

00:02:54.800 --> 00:02:55.521
Garden of Eden,

00:02:56.983 --> 00:03:00.366
why man was taken away from the garden

00:03:01.991 --> 00:03:03.972
why there were six thousand years between

00:03:04.012 --> 00:03:06.332
the time we were removed from the garden

00:03:06.812 --> 00:03:08.354
and the time we will be given the

00:03:08.413 --> 00:03:09.813
opportunity to return,

00:03:10.875 --> 00:03:11.754
when that will occur,

00:03:12.914 --> 00:03:15.116
and why it will occur.

00:03:16.537 --> 00:03:19.518
I think that this actually sets up one

00:03:19.538 --> 00:03:21.258
of the most profoundly important

00:03:21.399 --> 00:03:25.881
understanding of our purpose in the

00:03:26.520 --> 00:03:28.762
creation of the universe, why we're here.

00:03:30.225 --> 00:03:32.347
Since that's one of the great questions

00:03:32.387 --> 00:03:37.310
that mankind has probed for as long as

00:03:37.430 --> 00:03:40.890
we can plumb the depths of human

00:03:40.951 --> 00:03:42.592
understanding through writing,

00:03:42.632 --> 00:03:45.633
which dates back to just about six

00:03:45.674 --> 00:03:47.275
thousand years ago when this all

00:03:47.314 --> 00:03:49.756
transpired.

00:03:49.776 --> 00:03:50.616
I believe that,

00:03:50.635 --> 00:03:53.377
I think might be a better term,

00:03:53.557 --> 00:03:57.860
I think that I've unraveled the very

00:03:59.260 --> 00:03:59.640
question

00:04:00.882 --> 00:04:03.562
found the answer as to why we were

00:04:03.643 --> 00:04:04.263
conceived,

00:04:05.342 --> 00:04:07.924
how the story of what occurred in Adam

00:04:08.884 --> 00:04:11.425
explains why we were conceived,

00:04:12.145 --> 00:04:13.885
where we failed, where we went wrong,

00:04:14.967 --> 00:04:17.146
and when and why and how we will

00:04:17.166 --> 00:04:18.668
have the opportunity to make it right

00:04:18.708 --> 00:04:19.007
again.

00:04:20.747 --> 00:04:21.007
You see,

00:04:21.028 --> 00:04:25.350
what I've discovered is that Gan Eden,

00:04:25.750 --> 00:04:28.831
this protective and enclosed universe,

00:04:29.744 --> 00:04:34.627
sheltered garden conducive to life well a

00:04:34.687 --> 00:04:37.331
real place and something that likely

00:04:37.430 --> 00:04:41.093
occurred as we have read it in the

00:04:41.213 --> 00:04:44.997
opening book of the Towrah it is actually

00:04:45.076 --> 00:04:50.562
a microcosm for our planet earth earth is

00:04:50.581 --> 00:04:54.704
a very finely tuned highly protective and

00:04:54.786 --> 00:04:57.168
sheltered environment that's conducive to

00:04:57.228 --> 00:04:57.567
life

00:04:58.797 --> 00:05:00.038
could well be the only one in the

00:05:00.098 --> 00:05:03.339
universe.

00:05:03.439 --> 00:05:07.382
And what God is saying is that he

00:05:07.482 --> 00:05:10.084
created life in general and man

00:05:10.144 --> 00:05:12.824
specifically with a nesama,

00:05:12.865 --> 00:05:15.586
the one thing that makes mankind different

00:05:16.086 --> 00:05:18.069
than the rest of the animals that all

00:05:18.129 --> 00:05:19.509
have a nephesh soul,

00:05:20.269 --> 00:05:22.750
is that with a nesama, we can think,

00:05:23.351 --> 00:05:28.394
we can deduce right and wrong.

00:05:29.416 --> 00:05:33.978
We are enabled to determine what is

00:05:34.098 --> 00:05:35.620
productive and counterproductive,

00:05:35.680 --> 00:05:38.201
good and bad.

00:05:38.321 --> 00:05:41.783
Nesama is essentially our conscience or

00:05:41.862 --> 00:05:45.004
our nephesh soul is our consciousness.

00:05:45.644 --> 00:05:48.466
Consciousness simply gives an animal the

00:05:48.706 --> 00:05:50.567
ability to observe their environment and

00:05:50.607 --> 00:05:51.326
respond to it.

00:05:52.583 --> 00:05:55.285
A conscience enables us to think it

00:05:55.324 --> 00:05:59.288
through and make decisions about what we

00:05:59.329 --> 00:06:04.072
have witnessed that can lead us to things

00:06:04.093 --> 00:06:06.115
that are profoundly beneficial or

00:06:06.995 --> 00:06:07.656
destructive.

00:06:09.156 --> 00:06:11.059
It is the thing that brings us to

00:06:11.098 --> 00:06:11.399
God.

00:06:11.879 --> 00:06:14.562
And we are using it here to explain

00:06:15.562 --> 00:06:16.704
what happened.

00:06:16.744 --> 00:06:18.706
So Eden is a microcosm.

00:06:19.937 --> 00:06:23.218
of planet Earth and all of the big

00:06:23.278 --> 00:06:25.959
hype that the world's richest man,

00:06:26.279 --> 00:06:29.721
on paper anyway, has for going to Mars.

00:06:29.762 --> 00:06:32.663
We need to be a multi-planetary being or

00:06:32.723 --> 00:06:35.483
species or life is over for us and

00:06:35.524 --> 00:06:36.264
he's full of it.

00:06:36.324 --> 00:06:40.485
The fact is that Earth is conducive to

00:06:40.545 --> 00:06:40.886
life.

00:06:42.088 --> 00:06:46.529
mars the moon Venus any planet or moon

00:06:46.550 --> 00:06:52.194
within our reach is deadly toxic this

00:06:52.334 --> 00:06:59.156
planet is uniquely tuned for life and

00:06:59.216 --> 00:07:03.540
nowhere else within our grasp is and so

00:07:03.959 --> 00:07:05.341
yeah well then

00:07:06.434 --> 00:07:09.074
brought a man with a nesama conscience

00:07:09.595 --> 00:07:12.656
into this protective enclosure to tell us

00:07:12.675 --> 00:07:13.096
a story.

00:07:14.596 --> 00:07:18.617
And that story is that he wanted humankind

00:07:19.016 --> 00:07:20.016
to be observant.

00:07:21.017 --> 00:07:22.077
And you might say, why?

00:07:22.958 --> 00:07:24.077
What would be the purpose?

00:07:24.098 --> 00:07:26.918
The moment he has a nephesh soul,

00:07:26.959 --> 00:07:28.619
he is automatically observant.

00:07:29.720 --> 00:07:31.379
He will have eyes to see,

00:07:31.560 --> 00:07:34.221
ears to hear, touch, smell.

00:07:35.478 --> 00:07:38.721
He can know what's happening around him.

00:07:39.401 --> 00:07:44.346
So why would God say specifically that man

00:07:44.387 --> 00:07:46.408
was conceived to be observant?

00:07:47.550 --> 00:07:49.973
Ah, because there's so much to see.

00:07:50.392 --> 00:07:54.778
So much more to see than trees and

00:07:54.817 --> 00:07:58.841
streams and other animals and the like.

00:08:00.250 --> 00:08:01.850
Yahowah would have testimony that would go

00:08:01.911 --> 00:08:04.793
back to this time that he wanted us

00:08:04.833 --> 00:08:06.653
to closely examine and carefully consider.

00:08:07.173 --> 00:08:09.435
And that's just the beginning of it

00:08:09.475 --> 00:08:13.877
because the whole purpose is to calibrate

00:08:15.137 --> 00:08:18.439
a human such that we earn God's trust

00:08:19.500 --> 00:08:21.882
so that he can do as he most

00:08:21.961 --> 00:08:22.281
wants,

00:08:23.723 --> 00:08:26.564
which is to take us on journeys of

00:08:26.625 --> 00:08:28.665
exploration throughout history

00:08:29.329 --> 00:08:33.331
The known two trillion galaxies in our

00:08:33.432 --> 00:08:35.312
universe, it's likely many more than that.

00:08:36.955 --> 00:08:39.817
And the hundreds of billions of solar

00:08:39.876 --> 00:08:44.080
systems within each of those two trillion

00:08:44.720 --> 00:08:45.660
or more galaxies.

00:08:46.831 --> 00:08:50.494
even through the essence of what is now

00:08:50.553 --> 00:08:52.294
called dark energy and dark matter,

00:08:52.315 --> 00:08:54.937
so we can understand and see and explore

00:08:55.037 --> 00:08:55.837
it as well.

00:08:56.717 --> 00:08:58.158
He wants to show it off.

00:08:58.558 --> 00:09:00.961
He created something extraordinary,

00:09:01.520 --> 00:09:04.842
magnificent, and he wants to show it off,

00:09:04.942 --> 00:09:06.464
and he wants somebody to enjoy it with

00:09:06.504 --> 00:09:07.725
him.

00:09:07.745 --> 00:09:09.066
That's why we were conceived.

00:09:10.577 --> 00:09:14.000
And so Adam was specifically created to be

00:09:14.061 --> 00:09:16.923
observant so that he could be a good

00:09:17.024 --> 00:09:21.366
explorer when released from the garden and

00:09:21.407 --> 00:09:24.909
now released from this planet.

00:09:24.950 --> 00:09:29.234
But alas, Adam didn't measure up.

00:09:30.154 --> 00:09:34.958
Second, Yahowah wanted Adam to engage,

00:09:35.418 --> 00:09:36.821
to work, to make a contribution.

00:09:37.678 --> 00:09:39.379
He did not want to engage in a

00:09:39.440 --> 00:09:43.482
relationship with Adam such that Adam was

00:09:43.582 --> 00:09:44.524
a dependent.

00:09:45.283 --> 00:09:49.246
He's not looking for entitlements and to

00:09:49.386 --> 00:09:52.469
offer entitlements.

00:09:52.548 --> 00:09:52.769
No,

00:09:53.068 --> 00:09:55.071
God does not see his entitlements as a

00:09:55.150 --> 00:09:55.931
productive thing,

00:09:55.971 --> 00:09:57.613
but instead counterproductive.

00:09:59.173 --> 00:10:01.195
He wants the relationship to be mutually

00:10:01.215 --> 00:10:01.774
beneficial.

00:10:02.255 --> 00:10:05.957
He wants all parties to it to make

00:10:06.018 --> 00:10:06.719
a contribution.

00:10:07.693 --> 00:10:10.575
This was specified of Adam and Adam failed

00:10:10.634 --> 00:10:11.076
entirely.

00:10:11.096 --> 00:10:13.076
There is no indication that Adam did

00:10:13.417 --> 00:10:14.417
anything in the garden.

00:10:14.456 --> 00:10:15.256
He was a deadbeat.

00:10:15.317 --> 00:10:15.717
In fact,

00:10:15.738 --> 00:10:19.099
the terminology strongly suggests that he

00:10:19.139 --> 00:10:19.798
was lazy.

00:10:21.679 --> 00:10:23.041
And that's not what God's looking for.

00:10:24.301 --> 00:10:27.243
He's looking for people who are not only

00:10:27.302 --> 00:10:30.524
observant, good explorers,

00:10:31.125 --> 00:10:32.644
but those who will make a contribution

00:10:32.705 --> 00:10:33.326
along the way,

00:10:33.566 --> 00:10:35.567
who'll make the experience richer for

00:10:35.706 --> 00:10:36.287
everyone.

00:10:38.951 --> 00:10:40.192
God expects us to listen.

00:10:41.091 --> 00:10:42.793
Adam didn't do that very well either.

00:10:44.513 --> 00:10:45.933
And he certainly didn't respond

00:10:46.073 --> 00:10:48.174
appropriately to God's instructions.

00:10:49.115 --> 00:10:51.876
And Yahowah wants someone he can trust for

00:10:51.996 --> 00:10:57.399
us to be taken off this planet and

00:10:57.879 --> 00:11:00.320
into the fullness of the fourth,

00:11:00.679 --> 00:11:02.201
then into the fifth, sixth,

00:11:02.740 --> 00:11:04.341
and ultimately seventh dimensions.

00:11:05.666 --> 00:11:09.106
we have to be enriched and empowered and

00:11:09.547 --> 00:11:12.706
liberated beyond our imagination.

00:11:13.847 --> 00:11:16.388
With each increase and dimensionality

00:11:16.408 --> 00:11:18.328
being an infinite increase in

00:11:18.389 --> 00:11:21.828
possibilities and opportunities and

00:11:21.869 --> 00:11:22.489
choices,

00:11:24.490 --> 00:11:26.330
things to navigate and understand.

00:11:27.090 --> 00:11:29.490
And God simply can't do that in a

00:11:29.591 --> 00:11:33.312
universe filled with nuclear furnaces and

00:11:33.491 --> 00:11:34.631
black holes and

00:11:35.620 --> 00:11:38.761
Exploding nebula and all manner of things,

00:11:39.101 --> 00:11:44.244
particularly with time being a dimension.

00:11:44.825 --> 00:11:46.404
Because if we were to go back in

00:11:46.465 --> 00:11:49.167
time and mess things up,

00:11:49.226 --> 00:11:50.366
it could be catastrophic.

00:11:52.788 --> 00:11:54.389
And so God needs to know that if

00:11:54.428 --> 00:11:59.412
he gives us instructions, as he did Adam,

00:11:59.451 --> 00:12:01.312
that we will pay attention.

00:12:02.514 --> 00:12:04.596
And we can be trusted to do as

00:12:04.677 --> 00:12:07.979
he has instructed, which Adam was not.

00:12:10.559 --> 00:12:15.163
So what God realized is that man in

00:12:15.283 --> 00:12:20.267
a sheltered and protective environment had

00:12:20.326 --> 00:12:21.528
no opportunity to grow.

00:12:22.307 --> 00:12:23.950
There was no way for Adam to ever

00:12:24.009 --> 00:12:24.570
prove himself.

00:12:26.076 --> 00:12:28.476
To develop character, to develop resolve,

00:12:28.496 --> 00:12:31.798
to demonstrate that you have the

00:12:31.839 --> 00:12:35.341
wherewithal and can be relied upon to get

00:12:35.480 --> 00:12:39.183
up once you've fallen, to admit a mistake,

00:12:39.403 --> 00:12:43.405
correct it and move on wiser and better

00:12:43.446 --> 00:12:46.467
for it is something that is not possible

00:12:47.008 --> 00:12:49.028
in a protective and sheltered environment.

00:12:49.308 --> 00:12:52.091
That's why with overly protective parents,

00:12:52.171 --> 00:12:53.751
children don't develop and grow.

00:12:55.102 --> 00:12:56.844
We have to be allowed to fall.

00:12:56.903 --> 00:12:59.206
We have to be allowed to make mistakes.

00:13:00.066 --> 00:13:02.427
And we have to have a parent who

00:13:02.628 --> 00:13:04.769
is willing to tell us,

00:13:05.330 --> 00:13:06.770
this is the right choice,

00:13:06.870 --> 00:13:08.091
this is the wrong choice.

00:13:08.192 --> 00:13:09.893
If you make this choice,

00:13:09.913 --> 00:13:11.514
this is the things that will happen for

00:13:11.533 --> 00:13:11.594
you.

00:13:11.614 --> 00:13:12.514
If you make this one,

00:13:12.554 --> 00:13:15.096
then it's going to be harsh for you,

00:13:15.136 --> 00:13:18.538
but allow us to make those mistakes and

00:13:18.558 --> 00:13:19.320
then grow from them.

00:13:20.581 --> 00:13:22.162
That couldn't be achieved in the sheltered

00:13:22.182 --> 00:13:22.442
garden.

00:13:23.918 --> 00:13:26.041
There was no way for Adam to ever

00:13:26.360 --> 00:13:28.903
develop the character such that God could

00:13:28.923 --> 00:13:29.344
trust him,

00:13:29.403 --> 00:13:30.705
and there was no way for him to

00:13:30.764 --> 00:13:32.667
ever become interesting enough for God to

00:13:32.706 --> 00:13:34.128
say, let's go explore the universe.

00:13:34.668 --> 00:13:36.571
They were having trouble just exploring

00:13:36.610 --> 00:13:38.773
the garden.

00:13:38.793 --> 00:13:40.413
So it was God that ended the relationship.

00:13:40.875 --> 00:13:41.875
I don't think anyone, in fact,

00:13:41.975 --> 00:13:44.937
I'm certain no one has ascertained that,

00:13:44.977 --> 00:13:47.581
but it's quite obvious from the verb that

00:13:47.600 --> 00:13:48.562
God chose.

00:13:50.201 --> 00:13:54.083
when he announced to Adam that it's not

00:13:54.124 --> 00:13:55.164
good for man to be alone.

00:13:56.284 --> 00:13:57.285
The moment he said that,

00:13:57.365 --> 00:13:59.366
he had already made the decision that he

00:13:59.407 --> 00:14:00.547
was going to leave,

00:14:02.288 --> 00:14:04.908
distance himself from Adam and therefore

00:14:04.928 --> 00:14:05.350
the garden.

00:14:05.769 --> 00:14:07.630
So God made the decision to withdraw.

00:14:08.510 --> 00:14:11.273
And then he told Adam and us that

00:14:11.293 --> 00:14:12.673
it's not good for man to be alone,

00:14:12.712 --> 00:14:14.953
so he created woman for the benefit of

00:14:14.995 --> 00:14:15.254
man.

00:14:15.615 --> 00:14:17.216
So he wouldn't be alone when God left

00:14:17.255 --> 00:14:17.375
him.

00:14:18.115 --> 00:14:19.336
And then when...

00:14:20.379 --> 00:14:23.500
It is stated in English translations that

00:14:24.501 --> 00:14:26.303
God caused the man to fall asleep.

00:14:26.364 --> 00:14:28.225
It's not caused.

00:14:28.644 --> 00:14:29.765
That verb isn't a fall.

00:14:30.767 --> 00:14:32.828
It means that God caused the fall of

00:14:32.908 --> 00:14:33.288
man.

00:14:36.030 --> 00:14:37.851
And he explains why he did so.

00:14:40.995 --> 00:14:44.017
We had to be escorted out of the

00:14:44.057 --> 00:14:50.062
garden so that we could prove our worth

00:14:51.311 --> 00:14:53.173
by being devoted, by being steadfast,

00:14:53.212 --> 00:14:55.695
by working, by listening, by learning,

00:14:56.395 --> 00:14:59.639
by growing, by engaging, by contributing,

00:15:00.299 --> 00:15:04.924
by showing that we were worth the

00:15:04.945 --> 00:15:07.726
investment in time and we could be

